comment_Rating: Dr. Wells clearly demonstrates that he does not care much for his students when he does not listen to the feedback provided and simply says "I apologize" and moves on to the next thing. Expectations are also not clear because what is tested is not what is being taught.

SchoolName: Texas A&M University Health Science Center
comment_Rating: This class consisted mainly of group assignments and was extremely easy. There were a few easy participation questions every class and no tests, homework, or quizzes. Group project assignments were all quick and basically a completion grade. Easy A.

SchoolName: Texas A&M University Health Science Center
comment_Rating: Professor Kirkland's lectures are boring and hard to sit through. There are no tests but there are many assignments related to the final group project. She offers time during class to finish group assignments and to meet with your group. You also must participate and answer questions throughout the lectures every day for a participation grade.
